ind%20joy%20and%20creativity%20in%20our%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BDon't%20Swear%20at%20Work%3A%20The%20Rule%20Breakers'%20Guide%20to%20Workplace%20Brilliance%26quot%3B%20said%20she%20often%20tells%20people%20that%20gazing%20into%20space%20is%20a%20valuable%20use%20of%20their%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20always%20laugh%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIsn't%20it%20radical%20that%20that's%20funny%3F%20We're%20so%20conditioned%20to%20think%20that%20thinking%20isn't%20valuable%2C%20that%20it's%20funny%20even%20as%20a%20concept.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20limit%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20if%20your%20brain%20is%20encouraging%20you%20to%20look%20out%20the%20window%20for%20a%20while%2C%20it's%20wise%20to%20take%20heed%2C%20Hulse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYour%20brain%20is%20like%20a%20snow%20globe.%20If%20you%20shake%20up%20a%20snow%20globe%2C%20it's%20so%20noisy%2C%20and%20then%20it%20will%20start%20to%20slowly%20settle%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20need%20a%20settled%20snow%20globe%20in%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20solve%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b627287d-81e0-499b-bcf0-f2c1ef2ee7c3%5C%22%3EBurned-out%20girlboss%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHulse's%20first%20business%20was%20a%20large%20marketing%20agency%2C%20which%20she%20started%20aged%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20outside%2C%20she%20was%20immensely%20successful%2C%20landing%20huge%20clients%20such%20as%20Virgin%20Atlantic%20and%20IBM%2C%20opening%20offices%20in%20London%20and%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20expanding%20her%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20her%20late%2020s%20she%20started%20experiencing%20severe%20chest%20pains.%20After%20some%20tests%2C%20doctors%20concluded%20her%20heart%20was%20fine%2C%20but%20she%20was%20having%20panic%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHulse%2C%20a%20millennial%2C%20grew%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fburnout-women-executives-hustle-culture-girlboss-work-life-balance-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20%26quot%3Bgirlboss%26quot%3B%20era%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20hard%20work%20and%20success%20were%20prioritized%20over%20everything%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20thought%20I%20was%20handling%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20strong%20in%20resilience%20and%20all%20those%20things%20that%20women%20are%20conditioned%20to%20be%2C%20but%20my%20body%20was%20giving%20me%20all%20of%20these%20subtle%20cues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHulse%20realized%20she%20needed%20a%20change%2C%20so%20she%20pivoted%20to%20learning%20everything%20she%20could%20about%20the%20neuroscience%20of%20success%20and%20work%20and%20what%20makes%20us%20productive%20beings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20she's%20a%20confidence%20coach%20who%20trains%20people%20at%20top%20companies%2C%20including%20LinkedIn%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Spotify%2C%20to%20be%20more%20confident%20and%20how%20workplaces%20should%20be%20structured%20to%20bring%20out%20the%20best%20in%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20her%20top%20advice%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b946bc09-6748-44d8-8d0c-020936045a0e%5C%22%3E1.%20Don't%20ignore%20your%20emotions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHulse%20said%20many%20workplaces%20are%20still%20operating%20like%20they%20did%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20when%20emotions%20weren't%20as%20welcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20prioritizing%20intellectual%20rigour%20over%20our%20own%20personalities%20is%20not%20how%20humans%20naturally%20operate%2C%20leaving%20many%20people%20feeling%20like%20they're%20not%20themselves%20at%20work%2C%20or%20developing%20impostor%20syndrome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20feel%20as%20though%20we%20have%20to%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20personality%20transplant%20and%20suddenly%20be%20this%20serious%2C%20robust%20professional%2C%20it%20gets%20in%20our%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20Hulse%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20emotional%20beings.%20We%20make%20emotional%20decisions%2C%20em